content: Office skyscraper in Singapore **Lippo Center** is a 150 m (490 ft) [skyscraper](/wiki/Skyscraper) located at 78 [Shenton Way](/wiki/Shenton_Way) in [Singapore](/wiki/Singapore)'s [Downtown Core](/wiki/Downtown_Core). It was completed in 1990, has 34 floors, and is tied with two buildings of [The Gateway](/wiki/The_Gateway,_Singapore) as the 43rd-tallest building in the [city-state](/wiki/City-state). It was sold to Commerz Real AG for US$650 million in December 2007. Resource Pacific Holdings Pte Ltd, a company that is located on the 28th floor of the Lippo Center, currently houses the Honorary Consulate of [Jamaica](/wiki/Jamaica). - [List of tallest buildings in Singapore](/wiki/List_of_tallest_buildings_in_Singapore) This article about a Singapore building or structure is a stub.
